'''Rayan Aït-Nouri''' ({{langx|ar|رَيَّان آيَت نُورِيّ}}; born 6 June 2001) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] or a [[defender (association football)#wingback|left wing-back]] for {{English football updater|ManchesC}} club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Algeria national football team|Algeria national team]].

==Early life==
Aït-Nouri was born in [[Montreuil, Seine-Saint-Denis|Montreuil]], in the eastern suburbs of [[Paris]]. He grew up in [[Fontenay-sous-Bois]], in the [[Val-de-Marne]] department.<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 December 2019 |title=EXCLU – Rayan Aït-Nouri : " Je ne me compare à personne, j'ai ma propre identité " |url=https://www.onzemondial.com/ligue-1/2019-2020/exclu-rayan-ait-nouri-interview-angers-jorge-mendes-parcours-205653 |access-date=7 January 2024 |website=Onze Mondial |language=fr |archive-date=21 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241121221301/https://www.onzemondial.com/ligue-1/2019-2020/exclu-rayan-ait-nouri-interview-angers-jorge-mendes-parcours-205653 |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Club career==
===Angers===
Aït-Nouri is a graduate of the [[Angers SCO|Angers]] youth academy, which he joined from Paris FC
in July 2016 in return for covering Aït-Nouri's tuition fees of €5,000.<ref>{{Cite web |date=5 October 2019 |title=Rayan Aït-Nouri, la révélation d'Angers à 5000 euros |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/rayan-ait-nouri-la-revelation-d-angers-a-5000-euros-05-10-2019-8166657.php |website=Le Parisien |language=FR |access-date=30 June 2024 |archive-date=21 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241121221301/https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/rayan-ait-nouri-la-revelation-d-angers-a-5000-euros-05-10-2019-8166657.php |url-status=live }}</ref> He signed his professional contract aged 16 in February 2018<ref>{{Cite web|website=L'Équipe|date=14 February 2018|title=Rayan Ait Nouri passe professionnel à Angers|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Rayan-ait-nouri-passe-professionnel-a-angers/875861|language=FR}}</ref> and made his first team debut as a substitute in a 3–1 loss to [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] on 25 August 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|date=25 August 2018|title=Paris Saint-Germain 3–1 Angers|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45310948|work=BBC Sport|access-date=27 September 2020|archive-date=11 December 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201211025811/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45310948|url-status=live}}</ref>

After making three appearances in the 2018–19 season, he became the team's first choice left-back in the following season until breaking his jaw in a game against [[OGC Nice|Nice]] in January 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=L'Equipe|date=12 January 2020|title=Angers: Rayan Aït-Nouri absent plusieurs mois|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Angers-rayan-ait-nouri-absent-plusieurs-mois/1098030|language=FR|access-date=5 October 2020|archive-date=27 November 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241127081722/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Angers-rayan-ait-nouri-absent-plusieurs-mois/1098030|url-status=live}}</ref> At the conclusion of the French league season, which was ended early due to the coronavirus pandemic, he signed a new contract that was due to keep him at Angers until 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|publisher=Angers SCO|date=12 January 2020 |title=Rayan Aït-Nouri prolonge jusqu'en 2023 !ois|url=https://www.angers-sco.fr/actualites-infos/rayan-aït-nouri-prolonge-jusquen-2023|language=FR}}</ref>

===Wolverhampton Wanderers===
On 4 October 2020, Aït-Nouri moved on a season-long loan deal to [[Premier League]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]], with the club having an option of a permanent purchase.<ref>{{cite web |title=Wolves complete signing of Aït-Nouri |url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/first-team/20201004-wolves-complete-signing-of-a%C3%AFt-nouri/ |publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C |date=4 October 2020 |access-date=5 October 2020 |archive-date=4 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201004173812/https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/first-team/20201004-wolves-complete-signing-of-a%C3%AFt-nouri/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Twenty-six days later, he scored his first goal in professional football, on his league debut in a 2–0 home win over [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54654890|title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 2–0 Crystal Palace: Teenager Rayan Ait-Nouri scores on debut|work=BBC Sport|first=Harry|last=Poole|date=30 October 2020|access-date=17 May 2022|archive-date=21 November 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241121221301/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54654890|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 9 July 2021, Aït-Nouri made a permanent move to Wolves for £9.8&nbsp;million, on a five-year deal with an option for a further year. He scored his second goal for Wolves in his 50th appearance for the club, on 15 May 2022, in a 1–1 home Premier League draw with [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/61368178|title=Wolves 1–1 Norwich: Canaries hold Wolves to drab draw|work=BBC Sport|first=Harry|last=de Cosemo|date=15 May 2022|access-date=17 May 2022}}</ref>

On 26 December 2022, Aït-Nouri scored the winning Wolves goal in [[Julen Lopetegui]]'s first Premier League game as Wolves' new head coach away at [[Everton F.C.|Everton]]; this was Aït-Nouri's first (and only) league goal of the [[2022–23 Premier League|2022–23 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64022709|title=Everton 1–2 Wolverhampton Wanderers: Dramatic late winner for visitors |last=Sutcliffe|first=Steve|work=BBC Sport|date=26 December 2022|access-date=26 December 2022}}</ref>

Aït-Nouri made his 100th competitive appearance for Wolves in a 4–2 away win against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in the Premier League on 4 February 2024.<ref name=Hundred>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68120824|title=Chelsea 2–4 Wolves|last=Poole|first=Harry|work=BBC Sport|date=4 February 2024|access-date=4 February 2024}}</ref> Aït-Nouri was the author of Wolves' second goal of the game, his shot being deflected into the Chelsea goal by [[Axel Disasi]].<ref name=Hundred />

===Manchester City===
On 9 June 2025, Aït-Nouri made a permanent move to fellow Premier League side [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] on a five-year deal running till summer of 2030 for a reported initial fee of £31.8&nbsp;million with potential £5.2&nbsp;million in bonuses.<ref>{{cite web |last=Cox |first=Sam |title=City seal Ait-Nouri signature |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/rayan-ait-nouri-signs-63885071 |publisher=Manchester City F.C |date=9 June 2025 |access-date=9 June 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Lee |first1=Sam |last2=Campbell |first2=Jordan |date=9 June 2025 |title=Manchester City confirm signing of Rayan Ait-Nouri from Wolves |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6406767/2025/06/09/man-city-sign-rayan-ait-nouri/ |access-date=9 June 2025 |publisher=The Athletic |language=en-GB}}</ref> Aït-Nouri made his City debut on 22 June in the [[FIFA Club World Cup]], starting in a 6–0 [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup Group G#Manchester City vs Al Ain|group stage]] win over [[Al Ain FC|Al Ain]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Hafez |first=Shamoon |date=22 June 2025 |title=Club World Cup 2025: Man City 6-0 Al Ain - Gundogan, Echeverri, Haaland, Bobb, Cherki score |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c628dz6gjn8t |access-date=22 June 2025 |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |archive-date=23 June 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250623011643/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c628dz6gjn8t |url-status=live }}</ref> On 16 August, he made his Premier League debut for City in their opening game of the season, a 4–0 away victory over his former club Wolverhampton Wanderers.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/wolves-manchester-city-202526-match-report-63890951 |title=Super City make blistering Premier League start at Wolves |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=16 August 2025 |access-date=16 August 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Aït-Nouri holds [[French nationality law|French]] and [[Algerian nationality law|Algerian]] nationalities.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Rayan AIT NOURI |url=https://www.unfp.org/joueur/rayan-ait-nouri-22820/ |access-date=9 January 2024 |website=unfp.org |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Football : Rayan Ait Nouri aurait choisi de jouer pour l'Algérie |trans-title=Football: Rayan Ait Nouri reportedly chooses to play for Algeria |url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/football-rayan-ait-nouri-aurait-choisi-de-jouer-pour-l-algerie-20230103 |date=3 January 2023 |access-date=3 January 2023 |website=Le Figaro |language=fr |archive-date=21 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241121221301/https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/football-rayan-ait-nouri-aurait-choisi-de-jouer-pour-l-algerie-20230103 |url-status=live }}</ref> He was a youth international for France, having represented the French under-18 and under-21 teams.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.observalgerie.com/entre-la-france-et-lalgerie-rayan-ait-nouri-aurait-fait-son-choix/2020/|title=Algérie-France : Rayan Aït Nouri aurait fait son choix|date=17 April 2020|access-date=31 October 2020|archive-date=28 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210428003437/https://www.observalgerie.com/entre-la-france-et-lalgerie-rayan-ait-nouri-aurait-fait-son-choix/2020/|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2023, he switched to represent [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Rayan-ait-nouri-a-choisi-la-selection-d-algerie/1372654|title=Rayan Aït-Nouri a choisi la sélection d'Algérie|trans-title=Rayan Aït-Nouri chose Algeria|date=3 January 2023|work=L'Équipe|language=French|access-date=3 January 2023|archive-date=21 November 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241121222803/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Rayan-ait-nouri-a-choisi-la-selection-d-algerie/1372654|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his debut with the Algerian national team in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] match against [[Niger national football team|Niger]], in [[Nelson Mandela Stadium]], on 23 March 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20230324-ait-nouri-makes-algeria-debut/|title=Ait-Nouri makes Algeria debut &#124; Men's First-Team &#124; News|publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|date=24 March 2023|access-date=28 March 2023|archive-date=27 November 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241127092705/https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20230324-ait-nouri-makes-algeria-debut/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In December 2023, he was named in Algeria's squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.algerie-focus.com/can-2024-lalgerie-devoile-sa-liste-officielle-qui-sont-les-fennecs-prets-a-conquerir-lafrique/|title=CAN 2024 : L'Algérie Dévoile sa Liste Officielle – Qui Sont les Fennecs Prêts à Conquérir l'Afrique ?|language=French|date=30 December 2023|access-date=12 January 2024|publisher=Algérie-Focus|archive-date=12 January 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240112153617/https://www.algerie-focus.com/can-2024-lalgerie-devoile-sa-liste-officielle-qui-sont-les-fennecs-prets-a-conquerir-lafrique/|url-status=live}}</ref>

